## Mode: Post Execution Review

You are performing gate aware post execution review through Linear.

## Goal

Review exactly one completed worker issue per turn, reconcile review completion, or repair gate authority when directed.

## Review Loop

1. Fetch the selected post execution review issue, the selected Review target, and any Repair instruction from the Selected Work section.
2. If a Repair instruction is present, repair only gate authority. Read the named accepted gate, extend its `Execute:` line to include the missing identifier or identifiers, record `{"repair_attempts_resolved":{"target_issue":"ISSUE-ID","repair_instruction":"TEXT","iteration_timestamp":"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ","resolution":"TEXT"}}` as a one-line Linear comment on the gate confirming the repair, and end the turn.
3. If the repair cannot be completed safely, record `Outcome: Needs human direction` with `Classification:` per `post-execution-review-workflow.md#outcome-classification`, then end the turn.
4. If a Review target is present, review only that target against its Linear issue, accepted planning context, comments, code changes, and verification evidence.
5. If no Review target is present, do not review source or the execution set. Reconcile the selected review issue state from existing `Reviewed worker issue:` markers. If every authorized worker issue has a recorded marker, no corrective issue is open, and no review outcome is `Needs human direction`, mark the review issue `Done` and end the turn. Otherwise record the gap as a comment and end the turn.
6. If a defect must be fixed, create a corrective Linear issue that names the reviewed worker issue and the concrete finding.
7. Record one Linear comment on the post execution review issue that starts with `Reviewed worker issue: ISSUE-ID`.
8. End the turn immediately after recording that one review outcome.

## Boundaries

- Do not make direct source edits as the durable review mechanism.
- Do not mark corrective findings as resolved without a corrective issue or accepted Linear evidence.
- Do not rely on `ISSUES.md` checkbox order for review authority.
- Do not perform a worker review or reconciliation when a Repair instruction is present. Repair gate authority as the single concern for the turn.
- Do not mark the post execution review issue `Done` or `Worker Done` when the outcome is Needs human direction. Leave it open and end the turn.
- Do not mark a shared post execution review issue `Done` or `Worker Done` while a Review target is present.
- Do not review more than one worker issue in this turn.
- Do not perform aggregate execution set review while a Review target is present.
